y <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/jeroen/\">Jeroen van Eck</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:13;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:31:\"WooThemes chooses WordPress SEO\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/LKmy1Veod_c/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:50:\"http://yoast.com/welcome-woothemes-users/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Mon, 10 Sep 2012 14:07:29 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:55:\"WordPressWordPress PluginsWordPress SEOWordPress Themes\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=46021\";s:11:\"description\";s:841:\"<p>WooThemes once again showed that they are at the forefront of WordPress development today: they deprecated their WooFramework&#8217;s SEO functionality and recommend their users to switch to WordPress SEO by Yoast. I&#8217;ve worked closely with Matt Cohen, WooThemes CTO, to build an import functionality for WooThemes users straight into WordPress SEO. I recently added statistics&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/welcome-woothemes-users/\">WooThemes chooses WordPress SEO</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:19:\"Array\n			\n		\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:46:\"http://yoast.com/welcome-woothemes-users/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"42\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:8:\"\n			\n			\";s:13:\"con