re :)</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:12:\"Array\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:40:\"http://yoast.com/redesign-and-more/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"85\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:4:\"\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:14:\"yoast redesign\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:96:\"http://yoast.com/redesign-and-more/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=redesign-and-more\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:797:\"<p>Yoast keeps changing and growing in many, many ways. One of those is a redesign, which is now live. We&#8217;re finally using the theme framework we&#8217;ve been recommending to others for ages: StudioPress&#8217; Genesis. We used an external developer for most of the development, just because I&#8217;m too pressed for time myself and didn&#8217;t want&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/redesign-and-more/\">Redesign and more :)</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:18;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:30:\"Tag Optimization for WordPress\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/99yY97SLdX4/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:42:\"http://yoast.com/optimizing-tags/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Wed, 04 Jul 2012 14:51:30 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=45845\";s:11:\"description\";s:772:\"<p>In our website reviews we regularly encounter websites who&#8217;ve got just as many tags as posts, or 20,000 posts and 5,000 tags. This is undesirable as it means you&#8217;re not using tags to relate your posts together, which is what you should do. We usually tell them to optimize their tags but that&#8217;s easier to&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/optimizing-tags/\">Tag Optimization for WordPress</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:33:\"Array\n			\n		\n			\n		\n			\n		\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:38:\"http://yoast.com/optimizing-tags/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"86\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:16:\"\n			\n			\n			\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:204:\"Easy Tag Optimization with Term Optimizer by YoastWith selected tags, do the following: merge, delete &#38; redirect, shows posts with term, search &#38; tagDelete &#38; redirect tagSearch &#38; Tag posts\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:92:\"http://yoast.com/optimizing-tags/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=optimizing-tags\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:772:\"<p>In our website reviews we regularly encounter websites who&#8217;ve got just as many tags as posts, or 20,000 posts and 5,000 tags. This is undesirable as it means you&#8217;re not using tags to relate your posts together, which is what you should do. We usually tell them to optimize their tags but that&#8217;s easier to&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/optimizing-tags/\">Tag Optimization for WordPress</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:19;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:44:\"Twitter Cards, Open Graph & Social Meta Data\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/QeKlh469Q54/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:40:\"http://yoast.com/twitter-cards/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Sat, 16 Jun 2012 06:22:25 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:45:\"Social MediaOpenGraphTwitterWordPress Plugins\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=45800\";s:11:\"description\";s:791:\"<p>Two days ago, Twitter introduced a new system called Twitter Cards (see their docs). It allows site owners to enhance the expanded tweets Twitter creates for their site, much in the same was as  OpenGraph tags give site owners the chance to determine what their posts &#38; pages will look like when shared on Facebook. In&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/twitter-cards/\">Twitter Cards, Open Graph &#038; Social Meta Data</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:12:\"Array\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:36:\"http://yoast.com/twitter-cards/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"35\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:4:\"\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:20:\"Example Twitter Card\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:88:\"http://yoast.com/twitter-cards/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=twitter-cards\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:791:\"<p>Two days ago, Twitter introduced a new system called Twitter Cards (see their docs). It allows site owners to enhance the expanded tweets Twitter creates for their site, much in the same was as  OpenGraph tags give site owners the chance to determine what their posts &#38; pages will look like when shared on Facebook. In&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/twitter-cards/\">Twitter Cards, Open Graph &#038; Social Meta Data</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}}s:7:\"channel\";a:9:{s:5:\"title\";s:5:\"Yoast\";s:4:\"link\";s:16:\"http://yoast.com\";s:11:\"description\";s:17:\"Tweaking Websites\";s:13:\"lastbuilddate\";s:31:\"Fri, 15 Feb 2013 15:12:11 +0000\";s:8:\"language\";s:5:\"en-US\";s:2:\"sy\";a:2:{s:12:\"updateperiod\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:15:\"updatefrequency\";s:1:\"1\";}s:9:\"generator\";s:35:\"http://wordpress.org/?v=3.5.2-alpha\";s:10:\"feedburner\";a:4:{s:14:\"emailserviceid\";s:11:\"joostdevalk\";s:18:\"feedburnerhostname\";s:28:\"http://feedburner.google.com\";s:9:\"feedflare\";s:158:\"Subscribe with PodnovaSubscribe with NewsGatorSubscribe with NetvibesSubscribe with PageflakesSubscribe with My Yahoo!Subscribe with ODEOSubscribe with Google\";s:15:\"browserfriendly\";s:195:\"This is the combined feed for Yoast.com and the WordPress podcast. Subscribe now to get WordPress & Magento tips & tricks, helping you optimize your site for speed, search engines and conversion!\";}s:7:\"tagline\";s:17:\"Tweaking Websites\";}s:9:\"textinput\";a:0:{}s:5:\"image\";a:6:{s:5:\"tit