','O:9:\"MagpieRSS\":19:{s:6:\"parser\";i:0;s:12:\"current_item\";a:0:{}s:5:\"items\";a:20:{i:0;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:34:\"The focus keyword in WordPress SEO\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/q8_llL3WKzY/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:40:\"http://yoast.com/focus-keyword/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Thu, 21 Feb 2013 10:39:25 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:28:\"SEOWordPressKeyword Research\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=70957\";s:11:\"description\";s:763:\"<p>This question pops up time and again: why can I only add one focus keyword to your SEO plugin? People seem to think they have to set several keywords for each post. This post explores the reasoning behind that, very deliberate, decision. This is the input field I&#8217;m talking about: The focus keyword is not&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/focus-keyword/\">The focus keyword in WordPress SEO</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:30:\"Array\n			\n			\n		\n			\n		\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:36:\"http://yoast.com/focus-keyword/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"44\";}s:5:\"media\";a:3:{s:7:\"content\";s:12:\"\n			\n			\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:71:\"focus keywordFocus Keyword Suggest boxFocus keyword from Google Suggest\";s:19:\"content_description\";s:29:\"The focus keyword input field\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:88:\"http://yoast.com/focus-keyword/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=focus-keyword\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:763:\"<p>This question pops up time and again: why can I only add one focus keyword to your SEO plugin? People seem to think they have to set several keywords for each post. This post explores the reasoning behind that, very deliberate, decision. This is the input field I&#8217;m talking about: The focus keyword is not&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/focus-keyword/\">The focus keyword in WordPress SEO</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:1;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:42:\"500 Website Reviews, what we’ve learned!\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/8BRGdv5xwqA/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:46:\"http://yoast.com/500-website-reviews/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Tue, 22 Jan 2013 20:38:12 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:41:\"MagentoSEOUsability & ConversionWordPress\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=68173\";s:11:\"description\";s:793:\"<p>Over the last 3 years, we&#8217;ve sold &#38; delivered 500 website reviews, selling our 500th today. I&#8217;m incredibly proud of this and wanted to share some of our learnings in this post, as well as announce some changes. Some stats on our website reviews I started doing these website reviews in 2010, finishing 42 of&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/500-website-reviews/\">500 Website Reviews, what we&#8217;ve learned!</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/