r customers. While doing an analysis over the holidays of what we&#8217;d sold and how much time we spent supporting people, we found that people using the plugin on multiple sites were bound to ask&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/change-of-pricing-licensing-for-video-seo-plugin/\">Change of pricing / licensing for Video SEO plugin</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:12:\"Array\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:71:\"http://yoast.com/change-of-pricing-licensing-for-video-seo-plugin/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"59\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:4:\"\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:22:\"Yoast_avatar_Thijs_def\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:158:\"http://yoast.com/change-of-pricing-licensing-for-video-seo-plugin/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=change-of-pricing-licensing-for-video-seo-plugin\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:819:\"<p>As of last night, a license for our Video SEO plugin has become $20 cheaper for what&#8217;s probably about 90% of our customers. While doing an analysis over the holidays of what we&#8217;d sold and how much time we spent supporting people, we found that people using the plugin on multiple sites were bound to ask&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/change-of-pricing-licensing-for-video-seo-plugin/\">Change of pricing / licensing for Video SEO plugin</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:3;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:35:\"WordPress threaded comments and SEO\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/VX86_BWAsuU/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:62:\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-threaded-comments-and-seo/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Wed, 12 Dec 2012 13:51:35 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:22:\"WordPressWordPress SEO\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=61478\";s:11:\"description\";s:788:\"<p>Today my buddy Sander pointed out that he suddenly had pages showing as noindex,nofollow when he ran a spider across a site. A bit more researching learned us that WordPress automatically adds a noindex, nofollow robots meta tag to each URL that has ?replytocom in it. At first I (wrongly) thought this was new to&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-threaded-comments-and-seo/\">WordPress threaded comments and SEO</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:12:\"Array\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:58:\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-threaded-comments-and-seo/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"39\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:4:\"\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:51:\"remove replytocom variables option in WordPress SEO\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:132:\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-threaded-comments-and-seo/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=wordpress-threaded-comments-and-seo\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:788:\"<p>Today my buddy Sander pointed out that he suddenly had pages showing as noindex,nofollow when he ran a spider across a site. A bit more researching learned us that WordPress automatically adds a noindex, nofollow robots meta tag to each URL that has ?replytocom in it. At first I (wrongly) thought this was new to&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-threaded-comments-and-seo/\">WordPress threaded comments and SEO</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:4;a:14:{s:5:\"title\";s:47:\"Want SEOs to lose their job? Start doing yours!\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/WWcHVnArg3s/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:40:\"http://yoast.com/seo-paul-boag/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Tue, 11 Dec 2012 21:09:00 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:3:\"SEO\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=61382\";s:11:\"description\";s:808:\"<p>This morning, an article by Paul Boag was published on Smashing Magazine that got a few SEOs, including myself, all riled up. As Bill Slawski pointed out in the comments, Paul has written articles on SEO before. Paul, whom I respect tremendously for his web development work, obviously doesn&#8217;t &#8220;get&#8221; SEO and has evidently had&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/seo-paul-boag/\">Want SEOs to lose their job? Start doing yours!</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";s:6937:\"<p>This morning, <a href=\"http://www.smashingmagazine.com/2012/12/11/seo-the-inconvenient-truth/\">an article</a> by Paul Boag was published on Smashing Magazine that got a few SEOs, including myself, all riled up. As Bill Slawski pointed out in the comments, Paul has written articles on SEO <a href=\"http://boagworld.com/marketing/i-dont-get-seo/\">before</a>. Paul, whom I respect tremendously for his web development work, obviously doesn&#8217;t &#8220;get&#8221; SEO and has evidently had some bad experiences with the snake oil side of our trade over the years. Luckily he&#8217;s shown himself to be willing to learn and I hope to be part of that learning experience. But I also wanted to write about this as I think it&#8217;s important for our industry.</p>\n<p>His main argument, after you remove the link-bait title and the weird introduction, is that what <em>we</em> SEO&#8217;s call SEO these days, shouldn&#8217;t be called SEO as it should be called (decent) web development. I agree in large part with that statement. But here&#8217;s the kicker: if a web developer or web development agency fails (and they do, very often, very miserably), the client often doesn&#8217;t notice. The web developer often delivers a shiny new website with all the bells and whistles that the management asked about. The fact that technically, information structurally and architecturally, the entire site is a mess, will not be noticed by 99% of clients. At least&#8230;</p>\n<p>Not until they notice their analytics, or rather, the fact that their phone stops ringing. And they notice one specific thing: a big hole in their traffic, where organic traffic from search engines used to be. That&#8217;s when they call an SEO, because those are the people that know about search engines, right? That, Paul, is why we&#8217;re still called SEO&#8217;s. It&#8217;s a demand driven thing: the client wants more search traffic, so he / she searches for someone that delivers that to them. They don&#8217;t know that their web developer did a lousy job, it&#8217;s <em>our</em> job to tell that to them.</p>\n<p>In our <a href=\"http://yoast.com/hire-us/website-review/\">website reviews</a> we encounter, on a daily basis, websites that have been redesigned where the web developer / designer deemed it &#8220;not necessary&#8221; to do 301 redirects from the old URL structure to the new one. Where development environments are left open for Google to index and a few wrong links in the content mistakenly go <em>to</em> that development environment, causing havoc for the website in question. Websites where a fancy new faceted based search system causes 4.5 <em>billion</em> URLs (actual example), to be created and Google slowly indexes all of them, leaving the websites ranking in dust. I can go on for hours.</p>\n<p>My buddy <a href=\"http://theuws.com\">Richard</a> commented:</p>\n<blockquote><p>But what if they call it “inbound marketing”?</p></blockquote>\n<p>To which Paul said:</p>\n<blockquote><p>I much prefer that. It does not apply that sites should be optimised for search engines over users.</p></blockquote>\n<p>Sigh. First of all, if SEO means anything, it&#8217;s that we optimize the search engine, not the site. The term is a weird acronym, but people know it now, so we stick with it. You see, even when BMW wants to sell &#8220;mobility&#8221;, in the end they sell cars. We all <em>want</em> to sell website optimization, but in the end, people come to us for SEO. That we&#8217;ll give them website optimization as a result doesn&#8217;t matter.</p>\n<p>Also in the comments, <a href=\"http://www.seobythesea.com/about-seo-by-the-sea/\">Bill Slawski</a> said:</p>\n<blockquote><p>A person who uses things like keyword density and gateway pages is not an SEO, and never has been.</p>\n<p>But, if you need help with hreflang, canonical link elements, parameter handling, rel prev and next values for pagination, XML sitemaps for pages and images and videos and news, Google Plus authorship markup, Facebook’s Open Graph meta data, schema.org implementation, and many other issues that great content alone will not solve, an SEO can help you with those.</p></blockquote>\n<p>To his credit, Paul <a href=\"http://www.smashingmagazine.com/2012/12/11/seo-the-inconvenient-truth/#comment-985658\">responded</a> to that thanking Bill and stating that these:</p>\n<blockquote><p>&#8230; are not things I would expect any half decent web designers to do as part of their job.</p></blockquote>\n<p>Well to be honest Paul, I do expect a decent web designer to know that stuff and if he doesn&#8217;t, I expect him, and thus you, to stop commenting about SEO until you <em>do</em> know about that stuff. You obviously don&#8217;t, because If I take your article from 2010, linked above, as an example:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>you haven&#8217;t implemented <a href=\"http://yoast.com/push-rel-author-head/\">rel=&#8221;author&#8221;</a>;</li>\n<li>I can&#8217;t find an XML sitemap;</li>\n<li>most of the pages on his site except for singular posts and pages lack a decent <a href=\"http://yoast.com/canonical-url-links/\">rel=&#8221;canonical&#8221; link element</a>;</li>\n<li>there is no <a href=\"http://yoast.com/rel-next-prev-paginated-archives/\">rel=&#8221;prev&#8221; / rel=&#8221;next&#8221;</a> implementation on his archives;</li>\n<li>in fact, there is no decent pagination on those archives at all, and lastly;</li>\n<li>there is no schema.org markup.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>I could go on. So, Paul, you say in your article that SEO should be decent web development, but you obviously haven&#8217;t kept up to date with what decent web development is then. I have an easy fix for you though. If you install my (100% free as in beer) <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress/seo/\">WordPress SEO plugin</a> and take 2 minutes to configure it, 1 through 4 will be taken care of for you by that plugin, automatically. But if you do that I will take that as an acceptance that there is a very <em>convenient</em> truth about SEO. I trust I&#8217;ll get to convince you that SEO is worth while, but I think the world deserves more than just a comment on your post as a counter argument to your headline, which I know you now regret.</p>\n<p>Let this be the first step in me, and others, convincing you of the value in SEO. I very much hope to see an article from your hand in 6 to 12 months time stating you were wrong.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/seo-paul-boag/\">Want SEOs to lose their job? Start doing yours!</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/joostdevalk/~4/WWcHVnArg3s\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";}s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:36:\"http://yoast.com/seo-paul-boag/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"61\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:88:\"http://yoast.com/seo-paul-boag/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=seo-paul-boag\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:808:\"<p>This morning, an article by Paul Boag was published on Smashing Magazine that got a few SEOs, including myself, all riled up. As Bill Slawski pointed out in the comments, Paul has written articles on SEO before. Paul, whom I respect tremendously for his web development work, obviously doesn&#8217;t &#8220;get&#8221; SEO and has evidently had&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/seo-paul-boag/\">Want SEOs to lose their job? Start doing yours!</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:6937:\"<p>This morning, <a href=\"http://www.smashingmagazine.com/2012/12/11/seo-the-inconvenient-truth/\">an article</a> by Paul Boag was published on Smashing Magazine that got a few SEOs, including myself, all riled up. As Bill Slawski pointed out in the comments, Paul has written articles on SEO <a href=\"http://boagworld.com/marketing/i-dont-get-seo/\">before</a>. Paul, whom I respect tremendously for his web development work, obviously doesn&#8217;t &#8220;get&#8221; SEO and has evidently had some bad experiences with the snake oil side of our trade over the years. Luckily he&#8217;s shown himself to be willing to learn and I hope to be part of that learning experience. But I also wanted to write about this as I think it&#8217;s important for our industry.</p>\n<p>His main argument, after you remove the link-bait title and the weird introduction, is that what <em>we</em> SEO&#8217;s call SEO these days, shouldn&#8217;t be called SEO as it should be called (decent) web development. I agree in large part with that statement. But here&#8217;s the kicker: if a web developer or web development agency fails (and they do, very often, very miserably), the client often doesn&#8217;t notice. The web developer often delivers a shiny new website with all the bells and whistles that the management asked about. The fact that technically, information structurally and architecturally, the entire site is a mess, will not be noticed by 99% of clients. At least&#8230;</p>\n<p>Not until they notice their analytics, or rather, the fact that their phone stops ringing. And they notice one specific thing: a big hole in their traffic, where organic traffic from search engines used to be. That&#8217;s when they call an SEO, because those are the people that know about search engines, right? That, Paul, is why we&#8217;re still called SEO&#8217;s. It&#8217;s a demand driven thing: the client wants more search traffic, so he / she searches for someone that delivers that to them. They don&#8217;t know that their web developer did a lousy job, it&#8217;s <em>our</em> job to tell that to them.</p>\n<p>In our <a href=\"http://yoast.com/hire-us/website-review/\">website reviews</a> we encounter, on a daily basis, websites that have been redesigned where the web developer / designer deemed it &#8220;not necessary&#8221; to do 301 redirects from the old URL structure to the new one. Where development environments are left open for Google to index and a few wrong links in the content mistakenly go <em>to</em> that development environment, causing havoc for the website in question. Websites where a fancy new faceted based search system causes 4.5 <em>billion</em> URLs (actual example), to be created and Google slowly indexes all of them, leaving the websites ranking in dust. I can go on for hours.</p>\n<p>My buddy <a href=\"http://theuws.com\">Richard</a> commented:</p>\n<blockquote><p>But what if they call it “inbound marketing”?</p></blockquote>\n<p>To which Paul said:</p>\n<blockquote><p>I much prefer that. It does not apply that sites should be optimised for search engines over users.</p></blockquote>\n<p>Sigh. First of all, if SEO means anything, it&#8217;s that we optimize the search engine, not the site. The term is a weird acronym, but people know it now, so we stick with it. You see, even when BMW wants to sell &#8220;mobility&#8221;, in the end they sell cars. We all <em>want</em> to sell website optimization, but in the end, people come to us for SEO. That we&#8217;ll give them website optimization as a result doesn&#8217;t matter.</p>\n<p>Also in the comments, <a href=\"http://www.seobythesea.com/about-seo-by-the-sea/\">Bill Slawski</a> said:</p>\n<blockquote><p>A person who uses things like keyword density and gateway pages is not an SEO, and never has been.</p>\n<p>But, if you need help with hreflang, canonical link elements, parameter handling, rel prev and next values for pagination, XML sitemaps for pages and images and videos and news, Google Plus authorship markup, Facebook’s Open Graph meta data, schema.org implementation, and many other issues that great content alone will not solve, an SEO can help you with those.</p></blockquote>\n<p>To his credit, Paul <a href=\"http://www.smashingmagazine.com/2012/12/11/seo-the-inconvenient-truth/#comment-985658\">responded</a> to that thanking Bill and stating that these:</p>\n<blockquote><p>&#8230; are not things I would expect any half decent web designers to do as part of their job.</p></blockquote>\n<p>Well to be honest Paul, I do expect a decent web designer to know that stuff and if he doesn&#8217;t, I expect him, and thus you, to stop commenting about SEO until you <em>do</em> know about that stuff. You obviously don&#8217;t, because If I take your article from 2010, linked above, as an example:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>you haven&#8217;t implemented <a href=\"http://yoast.com/push-rel-author-head/\">rel=&#8221;author&#8221;</a>;</li>\n<li>I can&#8217;t find an XML sitemap;</li>\n<li>most of the pages on his site except for singular posts and pages lack a decent <a href=\"http://yoast.com/canonical-url-links/\">rel=&#8221;canonical&#8221; link element</a>;</li>\n<li>there is no <a href=\"http://yoast.com/rel-next-prev-paginated-archives/\">rel=&#8221;prev&#8221; / rel=&#8221;next&#8221;</a> implementation on his archives;</li>\n<li>in fact, there is no decent pagination on those archives at all, and lastly;</li>\n<li>there is no schema.org markup.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>I could go on. So, Paul, you say in your article that SEO should be decent web development, but you obviously haven&#8217;t kept up to date with what decent web development is then. I have an easy fix for you though. If you install my (100% free as in beer) <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress/seo/\">WordPress SEO plugin</a> and take 2 minutes to configure it, 1 through 4 will be taken care of for you by that plugin, automatically. But if you do that I will take that as an acceptance that there is a very <em>convenient</em> truth about SEO. I trust I&#8217;ll get to convince you that SEO is worth while, but I think the world deserves more than just a comment on your post as a counter argument to your headline, which I know you now regret.</p>\n<p>Let this be the first step in me, and others, convincing you of the value in SEO. I very much hope to see an article from your hand in 6 to 12 months time stating you were wrong.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/seo-paul-boag/\">Want SEOs to lose their job? Start doing yours!</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/joostdevalk/~4/WWcHVnArg3s\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";}i:5;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:44:\"WordPress SEO, more secure than ever before.\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/JSZwFzQzmn4/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:59:\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-seo-sucuri-safe-plugin/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Fri, 07 Dec 2012 16:05:06 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:39:\"WordPressWordPress PluginsWordPress SEO\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=60400\";s:11:\"description\";s:777:\"<p>One of the benefits of making money on paid plugins is that you can more easily spend money for other people to look at and even better, review your plugins. Today is the first result of what might become a somewhat longer tradition: WordPress SEO is now a Sucuri Safe Plugin. What this means? It&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-seo-sucuri-safe-plugin/\">WordPress SEO, more secure than ever before.</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:12:\"Array\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:55:\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-seo-sucuri-safe-plugin/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"25\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:4:\"\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:22:\"Sucuri Approved Plugin\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:126:\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-seo-sucuri-safe-plugin/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=wordpress-seo-sucuri-safe-plugin\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:777:\"<p>One of the benefits of making money on paid plugins is that you can more easily spend money for other people to look at and even better, review your plugins. Today is the first result of what might become a somewhat longer tradition: WordPress SEO is now a Sucuri Safe Plugin. What this means? It&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-seo-sucuri-safe-plugin/\">WordPress SEO, more secure than ever before.</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:6;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:25:\"Jetpack and WordPress SEO\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/b2wq4qeZAeo/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:52:\"http://yoast.com/jetpack-and-wordpress-seo/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Thu, 29 Nov 2012 09:11:01 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:39:\"WordPressWordPress PluginsWordPress SEO\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=57679\";s:11:\"description\";s:791:\"<p>The Jetpack plugin for WordPress has quite a few nice bits and pieces. There&#8217;s one issue: the developers at Automattic seem to think they&#8217;re alone in the world. In their last release, they enabled OpenGraph tags by default with no setting to disable it. Even when you already have WordPress SEO enabled and OpenGraph enabled&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/jetpack-and-wordpress-seo/\">Jetpack and WordPress SEO</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:12:\"Array\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:48:\"http://yoast.com/jetpack-and-wordpress-seo/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"85\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:4:\"\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:7:\"Jetpack\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:112:\"http://yoast.com/jetpack-and-wordpress-seo/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=jetpack-and-wordpress-seo\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:791:\"<p>The Jetpack plugin for WordPress has quite a few nice bits and pieces. There&#8217;s one issue: the developers at Automattic seem to think they&#8217;re alone in the world. In their last release, they enabled OpenGraph tags by default with no setting to disable it. Even when you already have WordPress SEO enabled and OpenGraph enabled&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/jetpack-and-wordpress-seo/\">Jetpack and WordPress SEO</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:7;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:33:\"WordPress SSL setup tips & tricks\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/UJSqyG-mFAg/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:46:\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-ssl-setup/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Tue, 20 Nov 2012 10:44:58 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:34:\"WordPressSSLUsability & Conversion\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=55906\";s:11:\"description\";s:782:\"<p>As we&#8217;re now running a plugin shop here on yoast.com, selling our Video SEO plugin, Tag optimizer and soon more, we also have a checkout page. I wanted that checkout page to run on https, for obvious reasons: people fill out their email and, depending on their payment method, their credit card details there. That&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-ssl-setup/\">WordPress SSL setup tips &#038; tricks</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:29:\"Array\n			\n		\n			\n		\n			\n		\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:42:\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-ssl-setup/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"17\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:16:\"\n			\n			\n			\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:88:\"WordPress SSL Setupextended validation SSL certificateW3TC MacCDN SSL settingsbroken SSL\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:100:\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-ssl-setup/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=wordpress-ssl-setup\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:782:\"<p>As we&#8217;re now running a plugin shop here on yoast.com, selling our Video SEO plugin, Tag optimizer and soon more, we also have a checkout page. I wanted that checkout page to run on https, for obvious reasons: people fill out their email and, depending on their payment method, their credit card details there. That&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-ssl-setup/\">WordPress SSL setup tips &#038; tricks</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:8;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:28:\"Video SEO for Wistia & Vippy\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/xy9iuCVh1bk/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:53:\"http://yoast.com/video-seo-for-wistia-vippy/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Tue, 13 Nov 2012 11:45:29 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=55142\";s:11:\"description\";s:777:\"<p>As promised in my post yesterday, today marks the day for a new release of my Video SEO plugin. This one brings support for yet another few plugins and some more: two new video hosting platforms: Wistia and Vippy. Wistia support: embedding and SEO The support for Wistia that is added in this release was on the&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/video-seo-for-wistia-vippy/\">Video SEO for Wistia &#038; Vippy</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:15:\"Array\n			\n		\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:49:\"http://yoast.com/video-seo-for-wistia-vippy/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"20\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:8:\"\n			\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:22:\"Wistia VideoVippy logo\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:114:\"http://yoast.com/video-seo-for-wistia-vippy/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=video-seo-for-wistia-vippy\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:777:\"<p>As promised in my post yesterday, today marks the day for a new release of my Video SEO plugin. This one brings support for yet another few plugins and some more: two new video hosting platforms: Wistia and Vippy. Wistia support: embedding and SEO The support for Wistia that is added in this release was on the&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/video-seo-for-wistia-vippy/\">Video SEO for Wistia &#038; Vippy</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:9;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:43:\"Why & how we sell premium WordPress plugins\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/ZKudSwI4BGA/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:52:\"http://yoast.com/selling-wordpress-plugins/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Mon, 12 Nov 2012 16:28:43 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:51:\"WordPressGoogle AnalyticsVideo SEOWordPress Plugins\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=54967\";s:11:\"description\";s:759:\"<p>About 2 months ago I released my first premium plugin for WordPress, my Video SEO plugin. A lot of people have asked me about the how and why of the selling and I thought it&#8217;d be a good idea to outline that in a post. Why sell premium WordPress plugins? Of course we got some&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/selling-wordpress-plugins/\">Why &#038; how we sell premium WordPress plugins</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:12:\"Array\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:48:\"http://yoast.com/selling-wordpress-plugins/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"40\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:4:\"\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:62:\"Google Analytics eCommerce tracking for Easy Digital Downloads\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:112:\"http://yoast.com/selling-wordpress-plugins/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=selling-wordpress-plugins\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:759:\"<p>About 2 months ago I released my first premium plugin for WordPress, my Video SEO plugin. A lot of people have asked me about the how and why of the selling and I thought it&#8217;d be a good idea to outline that in a post. Why sell premium WordPress plugins? Of course we got some&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/selling-wordpress-plugins/\">Why &#038; how we sell premium WordPress plugins</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:10;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:41:\"Video not showing in search results: why?\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/_PN0zHBKTVc/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:59:\"http://yoast.com/video-not-showing-search-results/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Thu, 01 Nov 2012 13:00:59 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:42:\"SEOVideo SEOWordPress PluginsWordPress SEO\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=52786\";s:11:\"description\";s:788:\"<p>In helping out people who are using my Video SEO plugin, I&#8217;m finding that some sites get &#8220;hit&#8221; by what I now call the &#8220;Not really a video page&#8221; effect. While it&#8217;s a pretty rare phenomenon I thought it was a good idea to share with the wider community and see what one can do&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/video-not-showing-search-results/\">Video not showing in search results: why?</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:12:\"Array\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:55:\"http://yoast.com/video-not-showing-search-results/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"36\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:4:\"\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:17:\"Video SEO notices\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:126:\"http://yoast.com/video-not-showing-search-results/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_