 Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:13;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:46:\"Google Analytics Dashboard for WordPress Blogs\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/WkB5HaRNB0I/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:53:\"http://yoast.com/google-analytics-dashboard/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Tue, 11 Sep 2012 09:11:47 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:14:\"Jeroen van Eck\";}s:8:\"category\";s:9:\"Analytics\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=45996\";s:11:\"description\";s:811:\"<p>One of the great new features of the ‘new Google Analytics’ are the custom dashboards. If you do not use them yet, you most definitely should. I’m using custom dashboards to measure SEO, PPC, ROI, conversions and more. I also made a custom dashboard for WordPress blogs using Yoast’s Google Analytics for WordPress plugin. I&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/google-analytics-dashboard/\">Google Analytics Dashboard for WordPress Blogs</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/jeroen/\">Jeroen van Eck</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:47:\"Array\n			\n		\n			\n		\n			\n		\n			\n		\n			\n		\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:49:\"http://yoast.com/google-analytics-dashboard/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"32\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:24:\"\n			\n			\n			\n			\n			\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:148:\"Google Analytics Dashboard for WordPress blogsCustom Variable Settings YoastNumber of posts readMost read postsMost read authorsMost read categories\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:114:\"http://yoast.com/google-analytics-dashboard/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=google-analytics-dashboard\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:811:\"<p>One of the great new features of the ‘new Google Analytics’ are the custom dashboards. If you do not use them yet, you most definitely should. I’m using custom dashboards to measure SEO, PPC, ROI, conversions and more. I also made a custom dashboard for WordPress blogs using Yoast’s Google Analytics for WordPress plugin. I&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/google-analytics-dashboard/\">Google Analytics Dashboard for WordPress Blogs</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/jeroen/\">Jeroen van Eck</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:14;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:31:\"WooThemes chooses WordPress SEO\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/LKmy1Veod_c/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:50:\"http://yoast.com/welcome-woothemes-users/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Mon, 10 Sep 2012 14:07:29 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:55:\"WordPressWordPress PluginsWordPress SEOWordPress Themes\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=46021\";s:11:\"description\";s:841:\"<p>WooThemes once again showed that they are at the forefront of WordPress development today: they deprecated their WooFramework&#8217;s SEO functionality and recommend their users to switch to WordPress SEO by Yoast. I&#8217;ve worked closely with Matt Cohen, WooThemes CTO, to build an import functionality for WooThemes users straight into WordPress SEO. I recently added statistics&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/welcome-woothemes-users/\">WooThemes chooses WordPress SEO</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:19:\"Array\n			\n		\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:46:\"http://yoast.com/welcome-woothemes-users/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"42\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:8:\"\n			\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:106:\"WooThemes chooses WordPress SEOWooThemes Import at work: check the import from Woothemes box, press import\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:108:\"http://yoast.com/welcome-woothemes-users/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=welcome-woothemes-users\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:841:\"<p>WooThemes once again showed that they are at the forefront of WordPress development today: they deprecated their WooFramework&#8217;s SEO functionality and recommend their users to switch to WordPress SEO by Yoast. I&#8217;ve worked closely with Matt Cohen, WooThemes CTO, to build an import functionality for WooThemes users straight into WordPress SEO. I recently added statistics&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/welcome-woothemes-users/\">WooThemes chooses WordPress SEO</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:15;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:23:\"Twitter Cards in action\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.