to do&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/twitter-cards-in-action/\">Twitter Cards in action</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:16;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:37:\"WordPress Archive Pages: the tutorial\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/ituadafIpro/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:50:\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-archive-pages/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Wed, 22 Aug 2012 13:26:41 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:38:\"WordPressWordPress SEOWordPress Themes\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=45944\";s:11:\"description\";s:816:\"<p>On any bigger site, you&#8217;ll get archive pages of some sort. Whether they are taxonomy or category archives, like this SEO category, Custom Post Type archives like this one for our WordPress plugin reviews or my speaking engagements, or even date archives: they all share the same common traits. In WordPress an archive will, by default, consist&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-archive-pages/\">WordPress Archive Pages: the tutorial</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:22:\"Array\n			\n		\n		\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:46:\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-archive-pages/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";