lf and instead of twitter.com, you&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/relative-urls-issues/\">Why relative URLs should be forbidden for web developers</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:12:\"Array\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:43:\"http://yoast.com/relative-urls-issues/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"60\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:4:\"\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:21:\"yoast &#8211; twitter\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:102:\"http://yoast.com/relative-urls-issues/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=relative-urls-issues\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:785:\"<p>Twitter is the website / web service most of us love and sometimes hate, a service that has become an integral part of most of our online identities. It&#8217;s one of the services we expect to be there when we Google ourselves or other people. So when you Google yourself and instead of twitter.com, you&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/relative-urls-issues/\">Why relative URLs should be forbidden for web developers</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:18;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:20:\"Redesign and more :)\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/Dzq5aIAuyBM/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:44:\"http://yoast.com/redesign-and-more/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Wed, 15 Aug 2012 11:47:45 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:8:\"Offtopic\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=45894\";s:11:\"description\";s:797:\"<p>Yoast keeps changing and growing in many, many ways. One of those is a redesign, which is now live. We&#8217;re finally using the theme framework we&#8217;ve been recommending to others for ages: StudioPress&#8217; Genesis. We used an external developer for most of the development, just because I&#8217;m too pressed for time myself and didn&#8217;t want&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/redesign-and-more/\">Redesign and more :)</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:12:\"Array\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:40:\"http://yoast.com/redesign-and-more/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"85\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:4:\"\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:14:\"yoast redesign\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:96:\"http://yoast.com/redesign-and-more/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=redesign-and-more\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:797:\"<p>Yoast keeps changing and growing in many, many ways. One of those is a redesign, which is now live. We&#8217;re finally using the theme framework we&#8217;ve been recommending to others for ages: StudioPress&#8217; Genesis. We used an external developer for most of the development, just because I&#8217;m too pressed for time myself and didn&#8217;t want&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/redesign-and-more/\">Redesign and more :)</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}i:19;a:15:{s:5:\"title\";s:30:\"Tag Optimization for WordPress\";s:4:\"link\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/99yY97SLdX4/\";s:8:\"comments\";s:42:\"http://yoast.com/optimizing-tags/#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Wed, 04 Jul 2012 14:51:30 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Joost de Valk\";}s:8:\"category\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:4:\"guid\";s:25:\"http://yoast.com/?p=45845\";s:11:\"description\";s:772:\"<p>In our website reviews we regularly encounter websites who&#8217;ve got just as many tags as posts, or 20,000 posts and 5,000 tags. This is undesirable as it means you&#8217;re not using tags to relate your posts together, which is what you should do. We usually tell them to optimize their tags but that&#8217;s easier to&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/optimizing-tags/\">Tag Optimization for WordPress</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"content\";s:33:\"Array\n			\n		\n			\n		\n			\n		\n			\n		\";s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:38:\"http://yoast.com/optimizing-tags/feed/\";}s:5:\"slash\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";s:2:\"86\";}s:5:\"media\";a:2:{s:7:\"content\";s:16:\"\n			\n			\n			\n			\";s:13:\"content_title\";s:204:\"Easy Tag Optimization with Term Optimizer by YoastWith selected tags, do the following: merge, delete &#38; redirect, shows posts with term, search &#38; tagDelete &#38; redirect tagSearch &#38; Tag posts\";}s:10:\"feedburner\";a:1:{s:8:\"origlink\";s:92:\"http://yoast.com/optimizing-tags/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=optimizing-tags\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:772:\"<p>In our website reviews we regularly encounter websites who&#8217;ve got just as many tags as posts, or 20,000 posts and 5,000 tags. This is undesirable as it means you&#8217;re not using tags to relate your posts together, which is what you should do. We usually tell them to optimize their tags but that&#8217;s easier to&#8230;</p><p><a href=\"http://yoast.com/optimizing-tags/\">Tag Optimization for WordPress</a> is a post by <a rel=\"author\" href=\"http://yoast.com/author/joost/\">Joost de Valk</a> on <a href=\"http://yoast.com\">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href=\"http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/\">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1:\"A\";}}s:7:\"channel\";a:9:{s:5:\"title\";s:5:\"Yoast\";s:4:\"link\";s:16:\"http://yoast.com\";s:11:\"description\";s:17:\"Tweaking Websites\";s:13:\"lastbuilddate\";s:31:\"Thu, 28 Feb 2013 21:11:35 +0000\";s:8:\"language\";s:5:\"en-US\";s:2:\"sy\";a:2:{s:12:\"updateperiod\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:15:\"updatefrequency\";s:1:\"1\";}s:9:\"generator\";s:35:\"http://wordpress.org/?v=3.5.2-alpha\";s:10:\"feedburner\";a:4:{s:14:\"emailserviceid\";s:11:\"joostdevalk\";s:18:\"feedburnerhostname\";s:28:\"http://feedburner.google.com\";s:9:\"feedflare\";s:158:\"Subscribe with PodnovaSubscribe with NewsGatorSubscribe with NetvibesSubscribe with PageflakesSubscribe with My Yahoo!Subscribe with ODEOSubscribe with Google\";s:15:\"browserfriendly\";s:195:\"This is the combined feed for Yoast.com and the WordPress podcast. Subscribe now to get WordPress & Magento tips & tricks, helping you optimize your site for speed, search engi