li>\n            <li>647-896-7400 (Chang)</li>\n          </ul>\n          <p>Email us at <a href=\'mailto:info@savewheelchairtrans.com\'>info@savewheelchairtrans.com</a>.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>','Home','','inherit','open','open','','14-revision','','','2013-01-25 07:02:12','2013-01-25 07:02:12','',14,'http://savewheelchairtrans.com/14-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(14,1,'2013-01-25 07:02:22','2013-01-25 07:02:22','<header class=\"header-background\"><img alt=\"wheelchair transportation\" src=\"wp-content/uploads/2013/01/wheelchair.jpg\" />\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"header-caption\">\r\n<h1>Wheelchair Accessible Transportation Services in Toronto.</h1>\r\n<p class=\"lead hidden-phone\">We are dedicated drivers trained to provide non-emergency wheelchair accessible transportation services to people with special needs and disabilities. We operate in Greater Toronto Area and beyond. <a href=\"/about/\"><button class=\"btn btn-primary\" type=\"button\">View More</button></a></p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"fb-like\" data-href=\"http://www.facebook.com/SaveWheelchairTrans\" data-send=\"false\" data-layout=\"button_count\" data-width=\"450\" data-show-faces=\"true\"></div>\r\n<div class=\"g-plusone\" style=\"padding-top: 1px;\" data-size=\"small\" data-href=\"https://plus.google.com/106099111215835488940\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</header>\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"marketing\">\r\n<h1>Your Satisfaction is Our Goal</h1>\r\n<p class=\"marketing-byline\">Need reliable wheelchair accessible transportation services? Look no further.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row-fluid\">\r\n<div class=\"hero-unit pointbox marketing span4\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<h2>Your Needs</h2>\r\nOur customers always come first. You can rely on us for your travel needs:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Medical Appointments</li>\r\n	<li>Dialysis</li>\r\n	<li>Rehabilitation</li>\r\n	<li>Physiotherapy</li>\r\n	<li>Social Activities</li>\r\n	<li>School Activities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"hero-unit pointbox marketing span4\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<h2>Our Services</h2>\r\nThe benefits of our services include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Professional Staff Members</li>\r\n        <li>Wheelchair Accessible Vans</li>\r\n	<li>24 / 7 Services</li>\r\n	<li>Flexible Door-to-Door Service</li>\r\n	<li>Best Rate</li>\r\n	<li>Maximum 5 Passengers</li>\r\n	<li>Provide Wheelchair if Needed</li>\r\n	<li><strong><em>Senior 10% Discount</em></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"hero-unit pointbox marketing span4\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n<h2>Contact Us</h2>\r\nCall us for inquiries or reservations.\r\n<ul class=\"lead\">\r\n	<li>647-239-5467 (Willy)</li>\r\n	<li>647-802-8727 (Peter)</li>\r\n	<li>647-896-7400 (Chang)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nEmail us at <a href=\"mailto:info@savewheelchairtrans.com\">info@savewheelchairtrans.com</a>.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Home','','publish','open','closed','','home','','','2013-02-16 01:13:38','2013-02-16 06:13:38','',0,'http://savewheelchairtrans.com/?page_id=14',0,'page','',0),(184,1,'2013-02-21 20:48:17','2013-02-22 01:48:17','I originally found the StopGap project from <a href=\"http://www.thestar.com/life/2013/01/03/toronto_businesses_get_free_ramps_and_new_customers_in_wheelchairs.html\">an article in Toronto Star</a>, and I found this project truly inspiring.\r\n\r\nStopGap is a non-profit organization to remove the physical barriers so that every person can access every space without worries. And their first project is the community ramp project: build bright colourful ramps with donated materials and install them at the stores that are willing to have the ramps in their doorsteps.\r\n\r\nWhat I really like about this project is the attention that this little ramp can get; the ramp itself is probably not the best wheelchair ramp design ever, but its vivid colour with StopGap website address on it attracts people\'s attentions walking by. Also I could see that these ramps also give positive images to the local stores that have them. I think this project could raise awareness of accessibility issues, which is what we need to make our neighbourhood more accessible.\r\n\r\nHere are some pictures that we took while we were at Stouffville. StopGap is expanding to install the ramps on other towns, and you can see the full list of locations <a href=\"http://www.stopgapblog.blogspot.ca/p/ramp-locations.html\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_166\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/b07ef10a5cfd11e2a52022000a1f9e5e_7.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-166\" alt=\"yellow ramp\" src=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/b07ef10a5cfd11e2a52022000a1f9e5e_7-300x300.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a> yellow ramp.[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-bFFC2OkssPk/UR8ByBZgzjI/AAAAAAAAAOk/2FDp-lAcrnI/s525/6da8099c5cfe11e2b68522000a1fb1ee_7.jpg\"><img alt=\"ramps\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-bFFC2OkssPk/UR8ByBZgzjI/AAAAAAAAAOk/2FDp-lAcrnI/s525/6da8099c5cfe11e2b68522000a1fb1ee_7.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a> ramps[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-c3E5Cj87YnI/UR8ByK_OV0I/AAAAAAAAAOo/XD_glhxsW9A/s525/7d250a5a5cfe11e2aacd22000a1f932c_7.jpg\"><img alt=\"red ramp\" src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-c3E5Cj87YnI/UR8ByK_OV0I/AAAAAAAAAOo/XD_glhxsW9A/s525/7d250a5a5cfe11e2aacd22000a1f932c_7.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a> red ramp[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Kru9fTTzyQI/UR8BzG7qgyI/AAAAAAAAAO0/Ht7dSJQG2yo/s525/d6c0db205cfe11e292a022000a1faf61_7.jpg\"><img alt=\"stouffville go station\" src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Kru9fTTzyQI/UR8BzG7qgyI/AAAAAAAAAO0/Ht7dSJQG2yo/s525/d6c0db205cfe11e292a022000a1faf61_7.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a> stouffville go station[/caption]','The Community Ramp Project - StopGap','','inherit','closed','open','','165-revision-10','','','2013-02-21 20:48:17','2013-02-22 01:48:17','',165,'http://savewheelchairtrans.com/165-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(182,1,'2013-02-21 20:47:42','2013-02-22 01:47:42','I originally found the StopGap project from <a href=\"http://www.thestar.com/life/2013/01/03/toronto_businesses_get_free_ramps_and_new_customers_in_wheelchairs.html\">an article in Toronto Star</a>, and I found this project truly inspiring.\r\n\r\nStopGap is a non-profit organization to remove the physical barriers so that every person can access every space without worries. And their first project is the community ramp project: build bright colourful ramps with donated materials and install them at the stores that are willing to have the ramps in their doorsteps.\r\n\r\nWhat I really like about this project is the attention that this little ramp can get; the ramp itself is probably not the best wheelchair ramp design ever, but its vivid colour with StopGap website address on it attracts people\'s attentions walking by. Also I could see that these ramps also give positive images to the local stores that have them. I think this project could raise curiosity and awareness of accessibility issues, which is what we need to make our neighbourhood more accessible.\r\n\r\nHere are some pictures that we took while we were at Stouffville. StopGap is expanding to install the ramps on other towns, and you can see the full list of locations <a href=\"http://www.stopgapblog.blogspot.ca/p/ramp-locations.html\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_166\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/b07ef10a5cfd11e2a52022000a1f9e5e_7.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-166\" alt=\"yellow ramp\" src=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/b07ef10a5cfd11e2a52022000a1f9e5e_7-300x300.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a> yellow ramp.[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-bFFC2OkssPk/UR8ByBZgzjI/AAAAAAAAAOk/2FDp-lAcrnI/s525/6da8099c5cfe11e2b68522000a1fb1ee_7.jpg\"><img alt=\"ramps\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-bFFC2OkssPk/UR8ByBZgzjI/AAAAAAAAAOk/2FDp-lAcrnI/s525/6da8099c5cfe11e2b68522000a1fb1ee_7.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a> ramps[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-c3E5Cj87YnI/UR8ByK_OV0I/AAAAAAAAAOo/XD_glhxsW9A/s525/7d250a5a5cfe11e2aacd22000a1f932c_7.jpg\"><img alt=\"red ramp\" src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-c3E5Cj87YnI/UR8ByK_OV0I/AAAAAAAAAOo/XD_glhxsW9A/s525/7d250a5a5cfe11e2aacd22000a1f932c_7.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a> red ramp[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Kru9fTTzyQI/UR8BzG7qgyI/AAAAAAAAAO0/Ht7dSJQG2yo/s525/d6c0db205cfe11e292a022000a1faf61_7.jpg\"><img alt=\"stouffville go station\" src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Kru9fTTzyQI/UR8BzG7qgyI/AAAAAAAAAO0/Ht7dSJQG2yo/s525/d6c0db205cfe11e292a022000a1faf61_7.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a> stouffville go station[/caption]','The Community Ramp Project - StopGap','','inherit','closed','open','','165-revision-8','','','2013-02-21 20:47:42','2013-02-22 01:47:42','',165,'http://savewheelchairtrans.com/165-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(21,1,'2013-01-25 07:03:20','2013-01-25 07:03:20','<div class=\'container sentence page-picture\'>\r\n      <div class=\'pointbox aboutbox\'>\r\n        <h1>About Us</h1>\r\n        <div class=\'row\'>\r\n          <img class=\'span2\' src=\'../wp-content/uploads/2013/01/logo.jpg\' alt=\'SAVE Wheelchair Trans Logo\'>\r\n          <div class=\'offset1 span6\'>\r\n            <p>We, at SAVE Wheelchair Trans, provide non-emergency wheelchair accessible transportation services in Greater Toronto Area and surrounding regions including Barrie, Kitchener, and Niagara Falls.</p>\r\n            <p>SAVE Wheelchair Trans is owned and operated by a group of dedicated drivers trained to support passengers with special needs and disabilities. Our drivers will take your reservation calls, will get you anywhere you need to go in Ontario, and also will look forward to providing you a ride again next time.</p>\r\n            <p>Our mission is to provide high-quality, secure, and reliable services for our clients. We strive for your satisfaction from your doorstep to your destination. We ensure that you feel comfortable and safe while the service is provided. We also operate 24 hours and 7 days a week, so that we are always ready to get you to wherever you want, whenever you need.</p>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class=\'pointbox aboutbox\'>\r\n        <h2>Why Should You Choose Us</h2>\r\n        <div class=\'row\'>\r\n          <div class=\'span5\'>\r\n            <p>Our clients are important to us. Your satisfaction is our top-most priority. In order to satisfy your mobility needs, we are delivering high-quality, secure, and reliable transportation services.</p>\r\n            <p>Our services are based on the industry competitive flat-rate pricing structure. When you call, you will be given a quote detailing the exact cost of the trip, which is calculated using the total distance. We also offer exclusive 10% discount to seniors.</p>\r\n            <p>Our drivers are committed to satisfy the mobility needs of our clients with high-quality customer care and safety. You will be comfortable and safe during the trip, and you will feel as if you would be in your own vehicle.</p>\r\n            <p>We provide flexible door-to-door transportation services 24 hours and 7 days a week. You can rely on us to go anywhere, whenever you need. We also provide wheelchairs upon request. Just let us know and we will bring it to your location.</p>\r\n            <p>Our clients always come first. We offer the highest quality of transportation services with competitive flat-rate pricing. Our drivers are committed to ensure that we provide comfortable and secure services to our clients. Also you can rely on us 24 hours and 7 days a week, flexible and door-to-door services.</p>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <img class=\'span4\' src=\'../wp-content/uploads/2013/01/wheelchair-assisting.jpg\' alt=\'Reliable Transportation Services\'>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div id=\'coverage\' class=\'pointbox aboutbox\'>\r\n        <h2>Where We Can Go</h2>\r\n        <div class=\'row\'>\r\n          <div class=\'span9\'>\r\n            <p>Our wheelchair transportation services cover the entire <abbr title=\'Greater Toronto Area\'>GTA</abbr> and surrounding regions including Barrie, Kitchener, and Niagara Falls.</p>\r\n            <img src=\"http://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?size=1000x1000&sensor=false&path=fillcolor:0xAA000033%7Ccolor:0xFFFFFF00%7Cenc:{uyjGdjl_N__iApfxBasZpdkAx|p@fvpBzo}@fppAtenBspd@vla@mvrGu~eB|go@&key=AIzaSyBwZhwQk0SfA1G-JWSHagEEgiIXAflg6_g\" alt=\'Service Coverage\'>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>','About','','publish','open','closed','','about','','','2013-01-25 07:04:32','2013-01-25 07:04:32','',0,'http://savewheelchairtrans.com/?page_id=21',1,'page','',0),(22,1,'2013-01-25 07:03:09','2013-01-25 07:03:09','<div class=\'container sentence page-picture\'>\n      <div class=\'pointbox aboutbox\'>\n        <h1>About Us</h1>\n        <div class=\'row\'>\n          <img class=\'span2\' src=\'../wp-content/uploads/2013/01/logo.jpg\' alt=\'SAVE Wheelchair Trans Logo\'>\n          <div class=\'offset1 span6\'>\n            <p>We, at SAVE Wheelchair Trans, provide non-emergency wheelchair 