<header class=\'header-background\'>\r\n      <img src=\'wp-content/uploads/2013/01/wheelchair.jpg\' alt=\'wheelchair transportation\'>\r\n      <div class=\'container\'>\r\n        <div class=\'header-caption\'>\r\n          <h1>\r\n            Non-Emergency Wheelchair Accessible Transportation Services in <abbr title=\'Greater Toronto Area\'>GTA</abbr>.\r\n          </h1>\r\n          <p class=\'lead hidden-phone\'>\r\n            We are dedicated drivers trained to provide wheelchair-accessible transportation services to people with special needs and disabilities. We operate in Greater Toronto Area and beyond. <a href=\'/about/\'><button class=\'btn btn-primary\' type=\'button\'>View More</button></a>\r\n            <div class=\"fb-like\" data-href=\"http://www.facebook.com/SaveWheelchairTrans\" data-send=\"false\" data-layout=\"button_count\" data-width=\"450\" data-show-faces=\"true\"></div>\r\n            <div style=\'padding-top:1px\' class=\"g-plusone\" data-size=\"small\" data-href=\"https://plus.google.com/106099111215835488940\"></div>\r\n          </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </header>\r\n    <div class=\'container\'>\r\n      <div class=\'marketing\'>\r\n        <h1>Your Satisfaction is Our Goal</h1>\r\n        <p class=\'marketing-byline\'>\r\n          Need reliable wheelchair-accessible transportation services? Look no further.\r\n        </p>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\'container\'>\r\n      <div class=\'row-fluid\'>\r\n        <div class=\'hero-unit pointbox marketing span4\' style=\'text-align:left\'>\r\n          <h2>Your Needs</h2>\r\n          <p>Our customers always come first. You can rely on us for your travel needs:</p>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Medical Appointments</li>\r\n            <li>Dialysis</li>\r\n            <li>Rehabilitation</li>\r\n            <li>Physiotherapy</li>\r\n            <li>Social Activities</li>\r\n            <li>School Activities</li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class=\'hero-unit pointbox marketing span4\' style=\'text-align:left\'>\r\n          <h2>Our Services</h2>\r\n          <p>The benefits of our services include:</p>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Professional Staff Members</li>\r\n            <li>24 / 7 Services</li>\r\n            <li>Flexible Door-to-Door Service</li>\r\n            <li>Best Rate</li>\r\n            <li>Maximum 5 Passengers</li>\r\n            <li>Provide Wheelchair if Needed</li>\r\n            <li><strong><em>Senior 10% Discount</em></strong></li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class=\'hero-unit pointbox marketing span4\' style=\'text-align:left\'>\r\n          <h2>Contact Us</h2>\r\n          <p>Call us for inquiries or reservations.</p>\r\n          <ul class=\'lead\'>\r\n            <li>647-239-5467 (Willy)</li>\r\n            <li>647-802-8727 (Peter)</li>\r\n            <li>647-896-7400 (Chang)</li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n          <p>Email us at <a href=\'mailto:info@savewheelchairtrans.com\'>info@savewheelchairtrans.com</a>.</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>','Home','','inherit','open','open','','14-revision-3','','','2013-01-25 07:02:22','2013-01-25 07:02:22','',14,'http://savewheelchairtrans.com/14-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(31,1,'2013-01-25 07:03:20','2013-01-25 07:03:20','<div class=\'container sentence page-picture\'>\r\n      <div class=\'pointbox aboutbox\'>\r\n        <h1>About Us</h1>\r\n        <div class=\'row\'>\r\n          <img class=\'span2\' src=\'../wp-content/uploads/2013/01/logo.jpg\' alt=\'SAVE Wheelchair Trans Logo\'>\r\n          <div class=\'offset1 span6\'>\r\n            <p>We, at SAVE Wheelchair Trans, provide non-emergency wheelchair accessible transportation services in Greater Toronto Area and surrounding regions including Barrie, Kitchener, and Niagara Falls.</p>\r\n            <p>SAVE Wheelchair Trans is owned and operated by a group of dedicated drivers trained to support passengers with special needs and disabilities. Our drivers will take your reservation calls, will get you anywhere you need to go in Ontario, and also will look forward to providing you a ride again next time.</p>\r\n            <p>Our mission is to provide high-quality, secure, and reliable services for our clients. We strive for your satisfaction from your doorstep to your destination. We ensure that you feel comfortable and safe while the service is provided. We also operate 24 hours and 7 days a week, so that we are always ready to get you to wherever you want, whenever you need.</p>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class=\'pointbox aboutbox\'>\r\n        <h2>Why Should You Choose Us</h2>\r\n        <div class=\'row\'>\r\n          <div class=\'span5\'>\r\n            <p>Our clients are important to us. Your satisfaction is our top-most priority. In order to satisfy your mobility needs, we are delivering high-quality, secure, and reliable transportation services.</p>\r\n            <p>Our services are based on the industry competitive flat-rate pricing structure. When you call, you will be given a quote detailing the exact cost of the trip, which is calculated using the total distance. We also offer exclusive 10% discount to seniors.</p>\r\n            <p>Our drivers are committed to satisfy the mobility needs of our clients with high-quality customer care and safety. You will be comfortable and safe during the trip, and you will feel as if you would be in your own vehicle.</p>\r\n            <p>We provide flexible door-to-door transportation services 24 hours and 7 days a week. You can rely on us to go anywhere, whenever you need. We also provide wheelchairs upon request. Just let us know and we will bring it to your location.</p>\r\n            <p>Our clients always come first. We offer the highest quality of transportation services with competitive flat-rate pricing. Our drivers are committed to ensure that we provide comfortable and secure services to our clients. Also you can rely on us 24 hours and 7 days a week, flexible and door-to-door services.</p>\r\n          </div>\r\n          <img class=\'span4\' src=\'../wp-content/uploads/2013/01/wheelchair-assisting.jpg\' alt=\'Reliable Transportation Services\'>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div id=\'coverage\' class=\'pointbox aboutbox\'>\r\n        <h2>Where We Can Go</h2>\r\n        <div class=\'row\'>\r\n          <div class=\'span9\'>\r\n            <p>Our wheelchair transportation services cover the entire <abbr title=\'Greater Toronto Area\'>GTA</abbr> and surrounding regions including Barrie, Kitchener, and Niagara Falls.</p>\r\n            <img src=\"http://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?size=1000x1000&sensor=false&path=fillcolor:0xAA000033%7Ccolor:0xFFFFFF00%7Cenc:{uyjGdjl_N__iApfxBasZpdkAx|p@fvpBzo}@fppAtenBspd@vla@mvrGu~eB|go@&key=AIzaSyBwZhwQk0SfA1G-JWSHagEEgiIXAflg6_g\" alt=\'Service Coverage\'>\r\n          </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>','About','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-3','','','2013-01-25 07:03:20','2013-01-25 07:03:20','',21,'http://savewheelchairtrans.com/21-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(32,1,'2013-01-25 07:03:42','2013-01-25 07:03:42','<div class=\'container sentence page-picture\'>\r\n      <div class=\'row-fluid\'>\r\n        <div class=\'pointbox aboutbox span6\'>\r\n          <h1>Phone</h1>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>647-239-5467 (Willy)</li>\r\n            <li>647-802-8727 (Peter)</li>\r\n            <li>647-896-7400 (Chang)</li>\r\n          </ul>\r\n          <h2>Email</h2>\r\n          <p><a href=\'mailto:info@savewheelchairtrans.com\'>info@savewheelchairtrans.com</a></p>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>','Contact','','inherit','open','open','','24-revision-3','','','2013-01-25 07:03:42','2013-01-25 07:03:42','',24,'http://savewheelchairtrans.com/24-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(33,1,'2013-01-25 07:03:54','2013-01-25 07:03:54','','Blog','','inherit','open','open','','27-revision-3','','','2013-01-25 07:03:54','2013-01-25 07:03:54','',27,'http://savewheelchairtrans.com/27-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(35,1,'2013-01-25 07:06:36','2013-01-25 07:06:36','Which city has the highest demand for wheelchair taxi in Canada? Which countries do people search for wheelchair transportation on the internet?\r\n\r\nAt least <a href=\"http://www.google.ca/trends/\">Google Trends</a> sheds some lights on trying to answer some of these questions. Google exposes where and when the search happened the most given the search keyword. I tried \'wheelchair\'.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"500\"]<a href=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend1.jpg\"><img style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"search traffic for wheelchair\" src=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend1.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"428\" /></a> search traffic for \'wheelchair\'[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe page shows \'wheelchair\' worldwide search traffic since 2004 to present. We can see that the traffic came mostly from United States, but a lot of traffic also came from Canada as well. I wanted to see which city people searched for \'wheelchair\', so I clicked \"City\" link to see the data.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"398\"]<a href=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend2.jpg\"><img style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"the list of cities from where people searched for wheelchair\" src=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend2.jpg\" width=\"398\" height=\"387\" /></a> The list of cities from where people searched for \'wheelchair\'[/caption]\r\n\r\nNote that the number besides the blue bar represent the search volume relative to the highest point on the chart, which is always 100. So in this case the search traffic for \'wheelchair\' from Toronto is about two third of the traffic coming from Dublin. And Toronto is the only city listed here.\r\n\r\nWe can see from the page that wheelchair search traffic is steady, and also a lot of people who searched for \'wheelchair\' usually also searched for keywords like \'wheelchair accessible\', \'wheelchair rental\', \'electric wheelchair\', etc. Since we are a wheelchair accessible transportation company, I typed \'wheelchair taxi\' to see what is the search trend for this keyword.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"500\"]<a href=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend3.jpg\"><img style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"search trend for wheelchair taxi\" src=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend3.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"377\" /></a> search trend for \'wheelchair taxi\'[/caption]\r\n\r\nSurprisingly there isn\'t much traffic for this throughout Canada, but the most of traffic comes from British Columbia and Ontario only. The city-level information is not available for this keyword. I think the reason is that the search volume for this keyword is substantially smaller than \'wheelchair\' or other popular keywords, so the information is too granular to expose to public.\r\n\r\nThe keyword for \'wheelchair transportation\' shows the similar graph.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"500\"]<a href=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend4.jpg\"><img style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"wheelchair transportation\" src=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend4.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"370\" /></a> keyword \'wheelchair transportation\'[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe pattern looks similar to \'wheelchair taxi\' except that the traffic is now highly concentrated on Ontario. Still overall the search volume is very small.\r\n\r\nI think there are not much data to draw any conclusion in this case because there aren\'t much traffic for wheelchair transportation in general. But I think Google Trends is a handy tool to help assess what people search for the most and quickly see where and when people look for stuff.','Wheelchair on Google Trends','','publish','open','open','','wheelchair-on-google-trends','','','2013-02-01 01:28:17','2013-02-01 06:28:17','',0,'http://savewheelchairtrans.com/?p=35',0,'post','',0),(52,1,'2013-01-31 23:26:25','2013-02-01 04:26:25','Which city has the highest demand for wheelchair taxi in Canada? Which countries do people search for wheelchair transportation on the internet?\r\n\r\nAt least <a href=\"http://www.google.ca/trends/\">Google Trends</a> sheds some lights on trying to answer some of these questions. Google exposes where and when the search happened the most given the search keyword. I tried \'wheelchair\'.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"500\"]<a href=\"http://www.savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend1.jpg\"><img class=\"  \" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend1.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"428\" /></a> search traffic for \'wheelchair\'[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe page shows \'wheelchair\' worldwide search traffic since 2004 to present. We can see that the traffic came mostly from United States, but a lot of traffic also came from Canada as well. I wanted to see which city people searched for \'wheelchair\', so I clicked \"City\" link to see the data.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"398\"]<a href=\"http://www.savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend2.jpg\"><img class=\" \" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend2.jpg\" width=\"398\" height=\"387\" /></a> The list of cities from where people searched for \'wheelchair\'[/caption]\r\n\r\nNote that the number besides the blue bar represent the search volume relative to the highest point on the chart, which is always 100. So in this case the search traffic for \'wheelchair\' from Toronto is about two third of the traffic coming from Dublin. And Toronto is the only city listed here.\r\n\r\nWe can see from the page that wheelchair search traffic is steady, and also a lot of people who searched for \'wheelchair\' usually also searched for keywords like \'wheelchair accessible\', \'wheelchair rental\', \'electric wheelchair\', etc. Since we are a wheelchair accessible transportation company, I typed \'wheelchair taxi\' to see what is the search trend for this keyword.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"500\"]<a href=\"http://www.savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend3.jpg\"><img class=\" \" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend3.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"377\" /></a> search trend for \'wheelchair taxi\'[/caption]\r\n\r\nSurprisingly there isn\'t much traffic for this throughout Canada, but the most of traffic comes from British Columbia and Ontario only. The city-level information is not available for this keyword. I think the reason is that the search volume for this keyword is substantially smaller than \'wheelchair\' or other popular keywords, so the information is too granular to expose to public.\r\n\r\nThe keyword for \'wheelchair transportation\' shows the similar graph.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"500\"]<a href=\"http://www.savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend4.jpg\"><img class=\"  \" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend4.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"370\" /></a> keyword \'wheelchair transportation\'[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe pattern looks similar to \'wheelchair taxi\' except that the traffic is now highly concentrated on Ontario. Still overall the search volume is very small.\r\n\r\nI think there are not much data to draw any conclusion in this case because there aren\'t much traffic for wheelchair transportation in general. But I think Google Trends is a handy tool to help assess what people search for the most and quickly see where and when people look for stuff.','Wheelchair on Google Trends','','inherit','closed','open','','35-revision-7','','','2013-01-31 23:26:25','2013-02-01 04:26:25','',35,'http://savewheelchairtrans.com/35-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(46,1,'2013-01-26 20:06:30','2013-01-27 01:06:30','Which city has the highest demand for wheelchair taxi in Canada? Which countries do people search for wheelchair transportation on the internet?\r\n\r\nAt least <a href=\"http://www.google.ca/trends/\">Google Trends</a> sheds some lights on trying to answer some of these questions. Google exposes where and when the search happened the most given the search keyword. I tried \'wheelchair\'.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"500\"]<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend1.png\"><img class=\"  \" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend1.png\" width=\"500\" height=\"428\" /></a> search traffic for \'wheelchair\'[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe page shows \'wheelchair\' worldwide search traffic since 2004 to present. We can see that the traffic came mostly from United States, but a lot of traffic also came from Canada as well. I wanted to see which city people searched for \'wheelchair\', so I clicked \"City\" link to see the data.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"398\"]<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend2.png\"><img class=\" \" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend2.png\" width=\"398\" height=\"387\" /></a> The list of cities from where people searched for \'wheelchair\'[/caption]\r\n\r\nNote that the number besides the blue bar represent the search volume relative to the highest point on the chart, which is always 100. So in this case the search traffic for \'wheelchair\' from Toronto is about two third of the traffic coming from Dublin. And Toronto is the only city listed here.\r\n\r\nWe can see from the page that wheelchair search traffic is steady, and also a lot of people who searched for \'wheelchair\' usually also searched for keywords like \'wheelchair accessible\', \'wheelchair rental\', \'electric wheelchair\', etc. Since we are a wheelchair accessible transportation company, I typed \'wheelchair taxi\' to see what is the search trend for this keyword.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"500\"]<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend3.png\"><img class=\" \" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend3.png\" width=\"500\" height=\"377\" /></a> search trend for \'wheelchair taxi\'[/caption]\r\n\r\nSurprisingly there isn\'t much traffic for this throughout Canada, but the most of traffic comes from British Columbia and Ontario only. The city-level information is not available for this keyword. I think the reason is that the search volume for this keyword is substantially smaller than \'wheelchair\' or other popular keywords, so the information is too granular to expose to public.\r\n\r\nThe keyword for \'wheelchair transportation\' shows the similar graph.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"500\"]<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend4.png\"><img class=\"  \" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/trend4.png\" width=\"500\" height=\"370\" /></a> keyword \'wheelchair transportation\'[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe pattern looks similar to \'wheelchair taxi\' except that the traffic is now highly concentrated on Ontario. Still overall the search volume is very small.\r\n\r\nI think there are not much data to draw any conclusion in this case because there aren\'t much traffic for wheelchair transportation in general. But I think Google Trends is a handy tool to help assess what people search for the most and quickly see where and when people look for stuff.','Wheelchair on Google Trends','','inherit','closed','open','','35-revision-5','','','2013-01-26 20:06:30','2013-01-27 01:06:30','',35,'http://savewheelchairtrans.com/35-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(36,1,'2013-01-25 07:06:23','2013-01-25 07:06:23','Which city has the highest demand for wheelchair taxi in Canada? Which countries do people search for wheelchair transportation on the internet?\n\nAt least <a href=\"http://www.google.ca/trends/\">Google Trends</a> sheds some lights on trying to answer some of these questions. Google exposes where and when the search happened the most given the search keyword. I tried \'wheelchair\'.\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"500\"]<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-vGkw9sfBB3Q/UP4cWe7TiPI/AAAAAAAAAKI/iyawNB2TabE/s1001/trend1.png\"><img class=\"  \" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-vGkw9sfBB3Q/UP4cWe7TiPI/AAAAAAAAAKI/iyawNB2TabE/s1001/trend1.png\" width=\"500\" height=\"428\" /></a> search traffic for \'wheelchair\'[/caption]\n\nThe page shows \'wheelchair\' worldwide search traffic since 2004 to present. We can see that the traffic came mostly from United States, but a lot of traffic also came from Canada as well. I wanted to see which city people searched for \'wheelchair\', so I clicked \"City\" link to see the data.\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"398\"]<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-xOkwcQF7LZ4/UP4eI2iLYQI/AAAAAAAAAKg/ONDkAuteA14/s398/trend2.png\"><img class=\" \" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-xOkwcQF7LZ4/UP4eI2iLYQI/AAAAAAAAAKg/ONDkAuteA14/s398/trend2.png\" width=\"398\" height=\"387\" /></a> The list of cities from where people searched for \'wheelchair\'[/caption]\n\nNote that the number besides the blue bar represent the search volume relative to the highest point on the chart, which is always 100. So in this case the search traffic for \'wheelchair\' from Toronto is about two third of the traffic coming from Dublin. And Toronto is the only city listed here.\n\nWe can see from the page that wheelchair search traffic is steady, and also a lot of people who searched for \'wheelchair\' usually also searched for keywords like \'wheelchair accessible\', \'wheelchair rental\', \'electric wheelchair\', etc. Since we are a wheelchair accessible transportation company, I typed \'wheelchair taxi\' to see what is the search trend for this keyword.\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"500\"]<a href=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Jpaz_ppSMDk/UP4gVWHNfGI/AAAAAAAAAKw/Sm99x-tEdz8/s975/trend3.png\"><img class=\" \" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Jpaz_ppSMDk/UP4gVWHNfGI/AAAAAAAAAKw/Sm99x-tEdz8/s975/trend3.png\" width=\"500\" height=\"377\" /></a> search trend for \'wheelchair taxi\'[/caption]\n\nSurprisingly there isn\'t much traffic for this throughout Canada, but the most of traffic comes from British Columbia and Ontario only. The city-level information is not available for this keyword. I think the reason is that the search volume for this keyword is substantially smaller than \'wheelchair\' or other popular keywords, so the information is too granular to expose to public.\n\nThe keyword for \'wheelchair transportation\' shows the similar graph.\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"500\"]<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-lPiBW67-IkA/UP4hgZqsTgI/AAAAAAAAAK8/-8-X3JYQdIs/s977/trend4.png\"><img class=\"  \" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-lPiBW67-IkA/UP4hgZqsTgI/AAAAAAAAAK8/-8-X3JYQdIs/s977/trend4.png\" width=\"500\" height=\"370\" /></a> keyword \'wheelchair transportation\'[/caption]\n\nThe pattern looks similar to \'wheelchair taxi\' except that the traffic is now highly concentrated on Ontario. Still overall the search volume is very small.\n\nI think there are not much data to draw any conclusion in this case because there aren\'t much traffic for wheelchair transportation in general. But I think Google Trends is a handy tool to help assess what people search for the most and quickly see where and when people look for stuff.','Wheelchair on Google Trends','','inherit','open','open','','35-revision','','','2013-01-25 07:06:23','2013-01-25 07:06:23','',35,'http://savewheelchairtrans.com/35-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(37,1,'2013-01-25 07:06:26','2013-01-25 07:06:26','Which city has the highest demand for wheelchair taxi in Canada? Which countries do people search for wheelchair transportation on the internet?\r\n\r\nAt least <a href=\"http://www.google.ca/trends/\">Google Trends</a> sheds some lights on trying to answer some of these questions. Google exposes where and when the search happened the most given the search keyword. I tried \'wheelchair\'.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"500\"]<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-vGkw9sfBB3Q/UP4cWe7TiPI/AAAAAAAAAKI/iyawNB2TabE/s1001/trend1.png\"><img class=\"  \" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-vGkw9sfBB3Q/UP4cWe7TiPI/AAAAAAAAAKI/iyawNB2TabE/s1001/trend1.png\" width=\"500\" height=\"428\" /></a> search traffic for \'wheelchair\'[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe page shows \'wheelchair\' worldwide search traffic since 2004 to present. We can see that the traffic came mostly from United States, but a lot of traffic also came from Canada as well. I wanted to see which city people searched for \'wheelchair\', so I clicked \"City\" link to see the data.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"398\"]<a href=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-xOkwcQF7LZ4/UP4eI2iLYQI/AAAAAAAAAKg/ONDkAuteA14/s398/trend2.png\"><img class=\" \" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-xOkwcQF7LZ4/UP4eI2iLYQI/AAAAAAAAAKg/ONDkAuteA14/s398/trend2.png\" width=\"398\" height=\"387\" /></a> The list of cities