Built Environment Standards focus on removing barriers in public spaces and buildings. For the public spaces, however, the standard only applies to new construction and major changes to existing features. This excludes the already built hiking trails and parks that are not wheelchair-accessible.\r\n<h2>Resources</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\"><a href=\"http://www.e-laws.gov.on.ca/html/statutes/english/elaws_statutes_05a11_e.htm\">Text of the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act</a>.</span></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.e-laws.gov.on.ca/html/statutes/english/elaws_statutes_01o32_e.htm\">Text of the Ontarians with Disabilities Act</a>.</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.e-laws.gov.on.ca/html/regs/english/elaws_regs_070429_e.htm\">Text of the Accessibility Standards for Customer Service</a>.</li>\r\n	<li></li>\r\n</ul>','Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA)','','inherit','closed','open','','85-revision-20','','','2013-02-08 23:20:58','2013-02-09 04:20:58','',85,'http://savewheelchairtrans.com/85-revision-20/',0,'revision','',0),(107,1,'2013-02-08 23:21:01','2013-02-09 04:21:01','[caption id=\"attachment_88\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/aoda.gif\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-88 \" alt=\"The Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act.\" src=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/aoda-300x300.gif\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a> The AODA[/caption]\r\n\r\nYou might have heard about the news regarding <a href=\"http://www.thestar.com/business/small_business/people/2012/12/26/taking_proactive_steps_to_comply_with_the_aoda_is_a_smart_business_move.html\">the businesses trying to comply with Accessibility for the Ontarians with Disabilities Act (AODA)</a>, or you might even have heard about more specific examples of <a href=\"http://www.starbucks.ca/responsibility/diversity/aoda\">Starbucks announcing the 