u are inside the paid area, you can see the elevator next to the fare gate that leads to the subway platform, and you can also find the washroom, which is wheelchair-accessible. There are one wheelchair stall and two non-wheelchair stalls. The wheelchair stall is neither particularly cleaner nor dirtier than the other stalls.\r\n\r\nThere is also another elevator that leads to the upper level, where you take another elevator to the bus platform. I took another movie clip from the bus platform to the subway platform.\r\n\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9OY8ASFCOlw\r\n\r\nI am not a wheelchair user and there would be more stuff that I missed which the actual wheelchair users would find inconvenient, but I think there are two issues that need to be improved:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">The lift needs to be fixed unless it is intentional to call for assistance every time the lift is used.</span></li>\r\n	<li>The North American Life Centre does not have a clear sign how to enter the building with wheelchairs. Either the building should make its main entrance wheelchair-accessible, or it should provide an explicit sign for its alternative accessible entrances.</li>\r\n</ol>','Accessible Routes to Finch TTC Station Subway Platform','','inherit','closed','open','','128-revision-17','','','2013-02-12 01:51:40','2013-02-12 06:51:40','',128,'http://savewheelchairtrans.com/128-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(148,1,'2013-02-12 01:51:47','2013-02-12 06:51:47','[caption id=\"attachment_145\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/finch.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-145\" alt=\"Finch TTC Station\" src=\"http://savewheelchairtrans.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/finch-300x171.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"171\" /></a> Finch TTC Station[/caption]\r\n\r\nFinch TTC Station is the most northernmost station in Yonge-subway line and is wheelchair-accessible. I am not a wheelchair user, but I 