ou can see in the clips there is a life in the stair passage from the lower level of North American Life Centre to the lower concourse level of the station. The problem with this life is that you cannot get the lift to your level if it is on the other level.\r\n\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q20clUbej5I\r\n\r\nThe landing instruction of the lift seems outdated or does not clearly explain how I could get the lift to my level. The only button I did not press is \"Call for assistance\", which I would find it annoying if I had to call the service attendant every time I use the lift.\r\n\r\nOnce you are inside the paid area, you can see the elevator next to the fare gate that leads to the subway platform, and you can also find the washroom, which is wheelchair-accessible. There are one wheelchair stall and two non-wheelchair stalls. The wheelchair stall is neither particularly cleaner nor dirtier than the other stalls.\r\n\r\nThere is also another elevator that leads to the upper level, where you take another elevator to the bus platform. I took another movie clip from the bus platform to the subway platform.\r\n\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9OY8ASFCOlw\r\n\r\nI am not a wheelchair user and there would be more stuff that I missed which the actual wheelchair users would find inconvenient, but I think there are two issues that need to be improved:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 13px;\">The lift needs to be fixed unless it is intentional to call for assistance every time the lift is used.</span></li>\r\n	<li>The North American Life Centre does not have a clear sign how to enter the building with wheelchairs. Either the building should make its main entrance wheelchair-accessible, or it should provide an explicit sign for its alternative accessible entrances.</li>\r\n</ol>','Accessible Routes to Finch TTC Station Subway Platform','','inherit','closed','open','','128-revision-20','','','2013-02-13 01:04:31','2013-02-13 06:04:31','',128,'http://savewheelch